Mr Kinyua said the changes are meant to foster operational efficiency, expedite the implementation of various ground-breaking reforms, and introduce functional changes that shall make ministries and state departments more effective and better able to deliver on their mandates. 

“The changes are also in recognition of the momentous task of setting the foundation for building back better, as Kenya rebounds from the socioeconomic shocks of the coronavirus pandemic,” he said. The President has also merged Mining department with Petroleum. Wiper and ANC leaders insist that ODM chief should honour a Nasa agreement signed in 2017 The lender of last resort has now given the government a total of Sh14.8 billion since last year. A total of 114 ward representatives vote in favour of the draft. A litany of court cases put paid to the by-election by the IEBC that was to be held today.